Mycobacteriosis in aquarium animals, human risks: RFI 980911001157
[1
Date: Fri, 11 Sep 1998 09:27:07 -0400
From: Gary Smith <garys@vet.upenn.edu>

I can provide anecdotal (and partial) information only. While discussing
this problem with veterinary students during a Public Health Course at [the
University of Pennsylvania (USA) , one of the students volunteered that
her father (a surgeon) had had to excise the granuloma arising from human
mycobacteriosis on only two occasions in twenty years.
--
Gary Smith
